# PART 1 ‚Äì DNS (Most Important)

Login to **Hostinger ‚Üí Domain ‚Üí DNS Zone**

Add these records üëá
(Replace NOTHING except exactly as shown)

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Mail exchanger (MX)

| Type | Name | Value               | Priority |
| ---- | ---- | ------------------- | -------- |
| MX   | @    | mail.synerydev.site | 10       |

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Mail host A record

| Type | Name | Value          |
| ---- | ---- | -------------- |
| A    | mail | 223.185.41.255 |

---

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ SPF (prevents spam flag)

| Type | Name | Value                          |
| ---- | ---- | ------------------------------ |
| TXT  | @    | v=spf1 ip4:223.185.41.255 ~all |

---

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ DMARC (mail reputation)

| Type | Name   | Value            |
| ---- | ------ | ---------------- |
| TXT  | _dmarc | v=DMARC1; p=none |

---

Save all.

Wait **5‚Äì10 minutes**.

---

# PART 2 ‚Äì Install Mail Server on Pi

Run:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y postfix dovecot-imapd dovecot-pop3d
```

During Postfix setup choose:

‚Ä¢ Internet Site
‚Ä¢ System mail name ‚Üí `synerydev.site`

---

# PART 3 ‚Äì Configure hostname

```bash
sudo hostnamectl set-hostname mail.synerydev.site
```

Edit hosts file:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/hosts
```

Add:

```
223.185.41.255   mail.synerydev.site
```

Reboot:

```bash
sudo reboot
```

---

# PART 4 ‚Äì Create your first mailbox

```bash
sudo adduser you
```

Your first email becomes:

```
you@synerydev.site
```

---

# PART 5 ‚Äì Test mail

From Pi:

```bash
echo "My Pi Mail Server Works" | mail -s "Test Mail" yourgmail@gmail.com
```

If it arrives in Gmail inbox/spam ‚Äî your server is LIVE üåçüìß



